lead_paragraph: A moderate earthquake shook Northern California today, but no injuries or damage were reported, officials said. The tremor at 12:41 P.M. measured 4.1 on the Richter scale og ground motion and was centered about 12 miles east of Milpitas, the United States Geological Survey said.
